This year has been a weird one for me. Spending 3 months touring Europe and playing my music live was a surreal experience. Connecting with fans in countries I only dreamed of being able to travel to- let alone playing my music in. 

However where there are highs, there are also lows. After releasing ‘Astronaut in the Ocean’, I was thrown into a world I knew little about and in no way I mentally prepared for. Going into 2022 I was trying my best to pave my way as the artist I had always envisioned. However along with a popular song comes pressure to follow it up, peoples opinions, people trying to take creative control and direction of me and my music, the hateful messages, the backlash of being an Aussie artist gaining traction outside of your country. Along with being a massive introvert battling anxiety I had no idea how to manage. 

This year I felt moments of being pulled in directions that didn’t sit right or feel authentic to me. I definitely struggled to find my own lane and voice in an industry that tells you what you should be doing and will point out everything that’s wrong with you. 

The back end of this year I split from my major label and will move into 2023 as an independent artist back with my original team at @teamwrkrecords with complete creative control over my music again. I’m ready to share with my fans new music I’ve been working on and writing everything from the heart. Love it or hate it. It’s going to be me 100%. 
To the fans who have stuck with me - Thankyou. I’m growing and learning every day as an artist. See you all in 2023. 
Butterflies & Bandaids out tomorrow.

A BILLION @spotify streams on this track & we still going hard! When I wrote Astronaut In The Ocean I was still working in a corporate 9-5 job and doing music by night. I felt so far from where I wanted to be. The lyrics represent the day to day struggles I faced mentally but never really spoke about. 
I wanted it to connect with people but never imagined the global reach it would have. Grateful for every single stream and the fans who listen to my music daily! 🙏🏼🙏🏼 🙏🏼

Merry Christmas Everyone. A lot of awful things have happened this year to soo many people around the world. Be grateful for the house that you sleep in, be happy for the pool you can swim in, the friends that surround you and most importantly as my mum would say be thankful that you have two legs to walk on and 2 arms and hands to eat with. Thanks for all the support, eat well, have fun and have a safe end to the year. As always never give up on your dreams, Merry Xmas and a happy new year to come 🥳🎄 🐺
